<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10392450>
    dc:description "FIGURES 89–99. Neobisium (N.) petruzzielloi n. sp., male holotype, Grotta degli Sportiglioni (Avella, Campania) (unless otherwise stated). 89, epistome of carapace and right ocular area; 90, right chelicera, dorsal view; 91, male, same locality, 3.I.2022: fingers of right chelicera, dorsal view; 92, female, same data as holotype, movable finger of right chelicera, dorsal view; 93, anterior processes of right coxa I; 94, trochanter, femur and patella of right pedipalp, dorsal view; 95, male, Inghiottitoio del Lete (Letino, Campania): patella of right pedipalp, dorsal view; 96, male, Grotta del Caprone (Montella, Campania): patella of right pedipalp, dorsal view; 97, right pedipalpal chela, dorsal view; 98, same, antiaxial view, with magnified detail of teeth; 99, right leg IV, antiaxial view, with magnified detail of subterminal seta of telotarsus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10392450/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

